\section{Experimental Results}
Our evaluation follows the "Strict Baseline" protocol (2 episodes, 500 steps each), imitating the conditions established by Castro et al. [1]. The results demonstrate a transformative shift in LLM-driven defense, highlighting the efficacy of the Chain-of-Self-Correction (CoSC) mechanism.

\subsection{Primary Performance Matrix}
The central finding of our experiment is the achievement of performance parity between reasoning-based LLMs and specialized Reinforcement Learning (RL) experts. As detailed in Table \ref{tab:performance_matrix} and visually illustrated in Figure \ref{fig:paper_vs_ours}, the DeepSeek-R1-1.5b variant reached a mean reward of -477.5. This effectively surpasses the KEEP RL agent's prior state-of-the-art benchmark (-493.0) and demonstrates a dramatic leap over the original paper's hybrid baseline.

